-- Bank of Japan May Ease Policy If Yen Stays Around 85 Per Dollar, Dow Says
-- Aaron Sheldrick
-- 2010-07-19T07:53:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-19/bank-of-japan-may-ease-policy-if-yen-stays-around-85-per-dollar-dow-says.html

          
          
             The Bank of Japan may take steps to
ease monetary policy should the yen stay around 85 to the U.S.
dollar, Dow Jones Newswires reported, citing people familiar
with the deliberations of officials at the central bank.  
          
          


  


        